[bright tone]

00:16.500 --> 00:19.542
[tense jazzy music]

00:21.875 --> 00:28.917
♪ ♪

01:47.667 --> 01:50.625
- "You made your bed,
now lie in it."

01:51.875 --> 01:54.083
Can anybody tell me
what the fuck that means?

01:54.083 --> 01:56.333
You don't go to the trouble
of making your bed,

01:56.333 --> 01:58.417
smoothing out the sheets,
fluffing up the pillows,

01:58.417 --> 02:01.041
just to ruin it all
by lying down.

02:01.041 --> 02:03.166
The phrase should be,

02:03.166 --> 02:06.084
"you laid in your bed,
now make it."

02:06.084 --> 02:07.250
The point being,

02:07.250 --> 02:10.917
you got to be responsible
for your actions.

02:13.417 --> 02:15.000
[grunts]

02:15.000 --> 02:17.375
Responsible.

02:20.834 --> 02:23.875
[indistinct chatter]

02:30.834 --> 02:32.417
[bell ringing]

02:34.333 --> 02:37.083
[tense percussive tones]

02:37.083 --> 02:42.333
♪ ♪

02:42.333 --> 02:45.709
- Kareem, you know,
we never doubt your wisdom.

02:45.709 --> 02:47.375
- You're
the boss, Vern.

02:47.375 --> 02:49.042
- But why are you
talking to that Nazi?

02:49.042 --> 02:50.084
- That nigger?

02:50.084 --> 02:51.458
- Like it or not,

02:51.458 --> 02:53.375
that man is
a child of God.

02:53.375 --> 02:55.959
Now I have made
a commitment to Allah

02:55.959 --> 02:59.375
to defend the rights
of all prisoners inside of Oz,

02:59.375 --> 03:01.917
not just the ones of color.

03:01.917 --> 03:04.417
Not just the ones
who believe what we believe,

03:04.417 --> 03:06.166
or who pray as we pray.

03:07.291 --> 03:10.001
- That nigger's gonna
get me out of here.

03:11.084 --> 03:13.000
- Said is representing
Vern Schillinger?

03:13.000 --> 03:14.250
- Mm-hmm.

03:14.250 --> 03:16.500
- Didn't Nostradamus
predict this?

03:16.500 --> 03:18.667
Doesn't this mean
we're two steps closer

03:18.667 --> 03:20.458
to the end of
the fucking world here?

03:20.458 --> 03:23.625
- You faced Said in Hill's
hearing, didn't you, Pat?

03:23.625 --> 03:26.209
- Yeah, and I won, but this is
gonna be a jury trial.

03:26.209 --> 03:30.875
Said's a powerful speaker;
he could move those jurors.

03:30.875 --> 03:32.583
- So what happens next?

03:32.583 --> 03:34.875
- You and Tim will have
to give another deposition.

03:34.875 --> 03:36.417
- Great.

03:36.417 --> 03:39.000
- He'll want to know how you
set up and trapped Schillinger,

03:39.000 --> 03:41.834
and he's also gonna
bring up Scott Ross.

03:41.834 --> 03:43.834
So be ready.

03:49.291 --> 03:50.709
- That doesn't worry you

03:50.709 --> 03:52.126
that we're gonna be
questioned about Ross?

03:52.126 --> 03:53.375
- No, why should it?

03:53.375 --> 03:55.917
- Diane, the last time
I was asked

03:55.917 --> 03:58.875
if I knew anything
about the shooting, I said no.

03:58.875 --> 03:59.917
- Yeah?

03:59.917 --> 04:01.417
- Well, this time
I can't.

04:01.417 --> 04:02.542
- Why not?

04:02.542 --> 04:04.126
- Because now
I know the truth.

04:04.126 --> 04:05.417
- So?

04:05.417 --> 04:08.000
- I'll be under oath.
- So?

04:08.000 --> 04:10.209
- You want me
to perjure myself?

04:10.209 --> 04:12.166
- Tim, what I want and what you
do are usually not even close.

04:12.166 --> 04:13.417
- I just--

04:13.417 --> 04:15.417
- Look, can we just
cut the shit?

04:15.417 --> 04:18.166
You are gonna say you have
a conscience, right?

04:18.166 --> 04:20.041
A moral code.

04:20.041 --> 04:22.500
Seepage in
your cerebral cortex.

04:22.500 --> 04:24.917
And I am
gonna say, lie.

04:24.917 --> 04:28.333
If you love me,
if you ever loved me,

04:28.333 --> 04:30.500
then lie.

04:34.000 --> 04:37.125
Schillinger approached me
outside the library.

04:37.125 --> 04:40.126
He told me he would
pay me to kill Beecher.

04:40.126 --> 04:43.000
- And you agreed?

04:43.000 --> 04:46.084
- Yes, in order to stop him.

04:48.291 --> 04:52.001
- We have a tape recording
of you and Vern Schillinger.

04:53.792 --> 04:57.458
Vern:
So last night?

04:57.458 --> 04:59.000
- You wanted
Beecher dead, right?

04:59.000 --> 05:00.834
- Yeah,
I wanted him dead.

05:00.834 --> 05:02.583
- You'll pay me, right?
Two grand?

05:02.583 --> 05:05.291
- Yeah.

05:05.291 --> 05:08.208
- This was your second
conversation about Beecher.

05:08.208 --> 05:09.291
- Yes.

05:11.084 --> 05:13.792
- We don't have a recording
of the first one.

05:13.792 --> 05:16.542
Isn't it true at that time
you approached Schillinger?

05:16.542 --> 05:18.583
- No.

05:18.583 --> 05:20.208
- You never asked him

05:20.208 --> 05:22.583
how much he'd pay you
to kill Tobias Beecher?

05:22.583 --> 05:26.542
- No, that would be entrapment
and against the law.

05:26.542 --> 05:28.583
- You say he offered
to pay you money.

05:28.583 --> 05:31.166
Did he offer you
anything else?

05:31.166 --> 05:34.375
- He implied that
if I didn't help him,

05:34.375 --> 05:39.084
he would tell people
I killed Scott Ross.

05:39.084 --> 05:41.417
- Did that factor into your
decision to trick him?

05:41.417 --> 05:46.167
- No, because
it's not true.

05:46.167 --> 05:49.458
No matter what Schillinger says,
or thinks he saw,

05:49.458 --> 05:52.126
I killed no one.

05:53.001 --> 05:55.209
♪ ♪

05:55.209 --> 05:57.084
- So officer Wittlesey's,
in general,

05:57.084 --> 05:59.041
a trustworthy person.

05:59.041 --> 06:01.167
- Yes.

06:01.167 --> 06:02.959
- She's never
lied to you.

06:02.959 --> 06:05.167
- I didn't say that.

06:05.167 --> 06:07.041
- So she has
lied to you.

06:07.041 --> 06:08.750
- Mm-hmm.

06:08.750 --> 06:12.084
- Did she lie to you regarding
Vern Schillinger?

06:12.084 --> 06:14.417
- You mean him wanting
to kill Beecher?

06:14.417 --> 06:15.625
- Yes.

06:15.625 --> 06:16.834
- No.

06:16.834 --> 06:18.458
- So she told you
the absolute truth

06:18.458 --> 06:20.208
about her reasons
for accepting his offer.

06:20.208 --> 06:22.126
- I assume so.

06:22.126 --> 06:23.083
- You assume so?

06:23.083 --> 06:24.291
- Yes.

06:24.291 --> 06:25.959
- So was one of
those reasons

06:25.959 --> 06:28.083
the fact that Schillinger knew
Wittlesey murdered Ross?

06:28.083 --> 06:30.250
- You mean
did she say to me

06:30.250 --> 06:32.250
that was one of
her reasons?

06:32.250 --> 06:33.667
- Yes.

06:33.667 --> 06:34.709
- No.

06:37.291 --> 06:42.084
- McManus, did Wittlesey
murder Ross?

06:42.084 --> 06:43.500
- Murder?

06:43.500 --> 06:45.001
- Yes.

06:45.001 --> 06:47.042
To the best
of your knowledge,

06:47.042 --> 06:49.041
did Diane Wittlesey
shoot Scott Ross

06:49.041 --> 06:51.959
with the intention
of ending his life?

06:51.959 --> 06:57.250
♪ ♪

06:57.250 --> 06:58.291
- No.

07:05.458 --> 07:10.166
♪ ♪

07:10.166 --> 07:11.709
[door slams]

07:12.792 --> 07:14.001
- Well?

07:17.750 --> 07:20.166
[muffled hip-hop music]

07:20.166 --> 07:22.291
- You don't
have a case.

07:22.291 --> 07:24.041
- Will you
turn that down?

07:24.041 --> 07:26.250
- They have evidence,
witnesses,

07:26.250 --> 07:28.458
and the tape recording.

07:28.458 --> 07:31.208
- There's gotta be some legal
loophole, some technicality.

07:31.208 --> 07:35.167
- You will be convicted of
conspiracy to commit murder,

07:35.167 --> 07:37.083
and you will be sentenced
to ten more years.

07:37.083 --> 07:38.750
- Fuck, might
as well be life.

07:38.750 --> 07:40.875
I'll never see my kids.

07:40.875 --> 07:43.792
Come on, there's gotta
be some way out.

07:43.792 --> 07:45.417
What about Wittlesey
killing Ross?

07:45.417 --> 07:47.084
- Your word against theirs.

07:47.084 --> 07:48.667
And without proof,
your word is meaningless.

07:48.667 --> 07:50.208
- They got you, baby.

07:50.208 --> 07:51.959
- Will you mind your own
goddamn business!

07:51.959 --> 07:53.750
- Schillinger,

07:53.750 --> 07:55.667
I'm withdrawing
from your case.

07:55.667 --> 07:57.126
- No, you are not.

07:57.126 --> 07:59.417
You pull out, that only
compounds my guilt.

07:59.417 --> 08:01.375
- I will not fight
your lost battle.

08:04.001 --> 08:06.875
- You did this on purpose,
didn't you?

08:06.875 --> 08:08.542
To set me up.

08:08.542 --> 08:11.084
You agreed to be my lawyer
knowing you were gonna pull out,

08:11.084 --> 08:12.959
knowing that'd
make things worse.

08:12.959 --> 08:14.792
- Things couldn't
be worse.

08:14.792 --> 08:18.001
I wasn't sure before,
but now I know.

08:18.001 --> 08:21.667
You are guilty, truly guilty.

08:24.000 --> 08:25.166
- You used me.

08:25.166 --> 08:27.166
- And you used me.

08:27.166 --> 08:29.875
Life is balance.

08:29.875 --> 08:31.417
- Fucking nigger.

08:31.417 --> 08:33.042
- As-salaam alaikum.

08:33.042 --> 08:34.166
- [laughs]

08:34.166 --> 08:37.125
You just lost
the balance, baby.

08:38.458 --> 08:41.209
- Billy Shakespeare,
in his last will and testament,

08:41.209 --> 08:43.375
left his wife, Anne Hathaway
his, quote,

08:43.375 --> 08:47.125
"second best bed."

08:47.125 --> 08:50.417
Now Shakespeare had abandoned
Anne and the kids years before

08:50.417 --> 08:53.250
and had only come
back home to Stratford

08:53.250 --> 08:56.001
when his bones
had started to creak.

08:56.001 --> 09:00.250
Was the second best bed a joke
between a husband and wife,

09:00.250 --> 09:04.166
or was it Shakespeare's
ultimate "Fuck you"?

09:04.166 --> 09:06.167
[tea kettle whistling]

09:10.126 --> 09:12.084
- Hello.

09:12.084 --> 09:14.041
Did you
need something?

09:14.041 --> 09:15.500
- No.

09:15.500 --> 09:16.542
- Oh, I do.

09:16.542 --> 09:20.001
I need a friend.

09:20.001 --> 09:21.209
- That ain't
gonna be me.

09:21.209 --> 09:23.001
- Of course.

09:23.001 --> 09:26.208
I'm a convicted murderer,
you're not.

09:28.208 --> 09:31.084
- Let me
ask you something.

09:31.084 --> 09:33.001
Do you sleep
at night?

09:33.001 --> 09:34.709
- Yes.

09:34.709 --> 09:36.875
- How is that possible?

09:36.875 --> 09:39.625
Given what you did, that you
sleep through the night?

09:39.625 --> 09:42.625
- When people ask me
about my daughter's death,

09:42.625 --> 09:46.417
I tell them
it was an accident.

09:46.417 --> 09:48.083
But it wasn't
an accident.

09:48.083 --> 09:51.042
It was what
had to happen.

09:51.042 --> 09:53.375
It was what had to be.

09:53.375 --> 09:55.875
And so I sleep.

09:55.875 --> 09:58.084
I sleep good.

09:58.125 --> 10:01.167
[tense percussive tones]

10:01.167 --> 10:05.625
♪ ♪

10:05.625 --> 10:07.542
- Hey, Diane.

10:13.417 --> 10:16.792
