37:58.375 --> 38:00.209
- Hey, baby.

38:00.209 --> 38:03.583
- Dr. Prestopnik,
my wife, Shannon.

38:03.583 --> 38:06.208
- Pleasure
and a half.

38:16.875 --> 38:18.583
- You haven't been
to see me lately.

38:18.583 --> 38:21.042
- Yeah, I know.

38:21.042 --> 38:22.709
I've been busy.

38:22.709 --> 38:24.333
- Doing what?

38:24.333 --> 38:26.375
- Taking care
of your brother.

38:26.375 --> 38:28.959
He's a little out of control
these days.

38:28.959 --> 38:30.792
- Yeah, I called my cousin,
Matthew.

38:30.792 --> 38:33.209
He's gonna
take Cyril in.

38:33.209 --> 38:36.375
You and I, Shannon,
we're done.

38:36.375 --> 38:38.583
- What?

38:38.583 --> 38:40.333
- I don't want to be
married to you anymore.

38:40.333 --> 38:42.917
- Why?

38:42.917 --> 38:45.083
- I found
someone else.

38:45.083 --> 38:46.500
- [laughs] Oh, God.

38:46.500 --> 38:48.042
- Shannon...

38:55.250 --> 38:58.125
- Gloria, what
are you doing here?

38:58.125 --> 39:00.291
- I've gotta work, Tim.

39:00.291 --> 39:03.291
I got nothing else
right now.

39:03.291 --> 39:05.625
- You should
take a vacation.

39:08.792 --> 39:10.291
- Where?

39:10.291 --> 39:14.126
How far do I need to go to
get away from what happened?

39:18.041 --> 39:20.209
You know...

39:20.209 --> 39:22.542
we didn't have
the best marriage,

39:22.542 --> 39:26.208
Preston and I, too many games,
too many tests,

39:26.208 --> 39:29.375
too much pride,

39:29.375 --> 39:33.500
but...
we really loved each other.

39:35.417 --> 39:37.792
We really did.

39:37.792 --> 39:39.375
He was a good man.

39:45.209 --> 39:47.375
Why'd he
have to die?

39:53.583 --> 39:55.250
[brakes squeal]

40:08.917 --> 40:11.959
Hill: prisoner number
98P284,

40:11.959 --> 40:13.417
Cyril O'Reily,

40:13.417 --> 40:18.000
convicted July 1st '98,
murder in the first degree.

40:18.667 --> 40:21.041
Sentence, life.

40:21.041 --> 40:25.209
Up for parole
in sixty years.

40:27.209 --> 40:29.042
[indistinct chatter]

40:31.709 --> 40:35.083
♪ ♪

40:35.083 --> 40:36.291
- No!
- No!

40:36.291 --> 40:39.001
Preston is dead
because of me.

40:43.042 --> 40:47.583
♪ ♪

40:47.583 --> 40:49.041
[bell ringing]

41:02.209 --> 41:04.041
- Hey, Gloria,
you're back.

41:04.041 --> 41:05.375
Hi.
- Don't!

41:05.375 --> 41:07.041
- What?

41:13.333 --> 41:17.333
- I became a doctor
to help people.

41:17.333 --> 41:21.500
Now I know that
that sounds like a cliché,

41:21.500 --> 41:25.000
it sounds naive,
but it's true.

41:25.000 --> 41:29.041
I could have a fancy
practice anywhere,

41:29.041 --> 41:32.084
but instead
I chose to work at Oz.

41:33.625 --> 41:36.625
I saved your life,
O'Reily.

41:39.667 --> 41:41.750
And in return
you destroyed mine.

41:54.959 --> 41:58.125
- Your brother, Cyril,
confessed.

41:58.125 --> 42:00.208
- Shit.

42:00.208 --> 42:02.167
- Cops want
to interrogate you,

42:02.167 --> 42:05.458
although he's refusing to
implicate you in the murder.

42:05.458 --> 42:08.166
He's gonna take
the rap himself.

42:09.250 --> 42:10.667
- McManus...

42:13.126 --> 42:15.291
You gotta see
that I love her, man.

42:16.667 --> 42:20.126
- Love? What the fuck
do you know about love?

42:20.126 --> 42:23.166
- What do you know, huh?

42:23.166 --> 42:25.834
What do
any of us?

42:25.834 --> 42:28.333
- I know I's not a reason
to commit murder.

42:28.333 --> 42:31.750
- Yeah, well, then maybe you've
never really been in love.

42:32.291 --> 42:39.333
♪ ♪

42:44.001 --> 42:45.750
- Life is no
bed of roses.

42:45.750 --> 42:47.125
Then again,

42:47.125 --> 42:50.375
which of us really wants to
sleep on a bed of roses?

42:50.375 --> 42:52.709
You'd never get any rest.

42:52.709 --> 42:54.750
Every time
you toss and turn,

42:54.750 --> 42:56.917
you hit another thorn.

43:00.750 --> 43:02.208
[tires screeching]

43:06.083 --> 43:07.542
- Ahh!

43:09.917 --> 43:12.542
- Hey, hey,
hey, hey.

43:12.542 --> 43:14.041
You all right?

43:18.001 --> 43:19.959
Same nightmare,
huh?

43:19.959 --> 43:21.001
- Yeah.
- Wow.

43:21.709 --> 43:23.208
- I'm soaked.

43:23.208 --> 43:25.458
- Yeah, let's get you
out of those.

43:30.041 --> 43:31.750
Jesus.

43:39.500 --> 43:40.917
- Thanks.

43:40.917 --> 43:42.583
- We need to do something
about that tattoo.

43:42.583 --> 43:43.875
- Oh, yeah?

43:43.875 --> 43:46.208
What are we
gonna do?

43:49.208 --> 43:51.667
- I don't know.
Let me think of it, huh?

43:58.083 --> 43:59.417
You all right?

43:59.417 --> 44:01.001
- Yeah.

44:10.084 --> 44:17.126
♪ ♪

44:24.001 --> 44:25.417
- Good morning,
Tobias.

44:25.417 --> 44:26.583
- Good morning.

44:26.583 --> 44:29.667
- What's the matter?

44:29.667 --> 44:31.126
- Nothing.

44:31.126 --> 44:34.084
- Tobias, I see you
almost every single day.

44:34.084 --> 44:37.042
I know the difference
between nothing

44:37.042 --> 44:39.126
and nothing.

44:59.375 --> 45:02.209
- Two men shouldn't
love each other.

45:03.250 --> 45:08.875
They can't feel the same things
a man and a woman feel.

45:12.250 --> 45:16.291
I mean, if a guy has a lot
of bad shit happen to him

45:16.291 --> 45:19.959
and another guy
comforts him,

45:19.959 --> 45:22.291
I mean, that's,
that's all it is, right?

45:22.291 --> 45:25.250
I mean, that's
not love, right?

45:25.250 --> 45:29.333
- Well, some men in here are
homosexual and some need sex--

45:29.333 --> 45:32.250
- I'm not talking about sex;
I'm talking about love.

45:32.250 --> 45:34.041
I had sex
with Schillinger.

45:34.041 --> 45:36.667
It was brutal,
unloving.

45:38.042 --> 45:41.458
This is different.

45:45.084 --> 45:48.583
- Tobias, are you in love
with another man?

45:53.542 --> 45:55.125
- I think so, yeah.

45:55.125 --> 45:57.084
[gate buzzes]

45:57.084 --> 45:59.000
- 98B242,

45:59.000 --> 46:01.167
65R814,

46:01.167 --> 46:02.959
97B412,

46:02.959 --> 46:05.167
98K514.

46:05.167 --> 46:07.375
- All right, everybody,
into your cells.

46:07.375 --> 46:09.834
[bell ringing]

46:11.001 --> 46:13.125
- Got a surprise
for you.

46:13.125 --> 46:14.875
- A surprise?

46:14.875 --> 46:17.792
- I talked to a couple of guys
who know about tattoos.

46:17.792 --> 46:20.500
They said because yours was
burned on instead of inked,

46:20.500 --> 46:22.542
it can't be removed.

46:22.542 --> 46:24.792
- I could've told you that.

46:24.792 --> 46:27.042
- You hate
the swastika, right?

46:27.042 --> 46:29.125
- Yeah.

46:29.125 --> 46:31.417
- Okay, so then we
fill it in like that.

46:31.417 --> 46:32.667
- [scoffs]

46:32.667 --> 46:35.375
- Oh, okay, wait,
you don't like that?

46:35.375 --> 46:39.542
We'll be PROCEDURE.
We'll just do that.

46:39.542 --> 46:42.167
- That's crazy.
- Why crazy?

46:42.167 --> 46:44.042
- As much as I want to get rid
of the fucking thing,

46:44.042 --> 46:46.417
I remember how painful
it was going on.

46:46.417 --> 46:49.500
Both of those, it's a lot
of burned flesh.

46:49.500 --> 46:52.125
- Which leads

46:52.125 --> 46:55.083
to the second part
of my surprise.

46:57.209 --> 46:58.750
- What's that?
- Moonshine.

46:58.750 --> 47:01.417
101% pure alcohol.

47:01.417 --> 47:03.250
It's like
the old west,

47:03.250 --> 47:05.750
cowboy gets shot,
you gotta remove the bullet.

47:05.750 --> 47:07.417
You take a couple of snorts
of this shit,

47:07.417 --> 47:09.792
you're not gonna
feel anything.

47:09.792 --> 47:12.126
- There's only
one problem with that.

47:12.126 --> 47:14.084
I've been sober
for over a year now.

47:14.084 --> 47:15.750
- So what?

47:18.041 --> 47:20.625
- I'm an alcoholic.

47:21.583 --> 47:23.875
Every bad thing that's
ever happened to me

47:23.875 --> 47:27.083
has been as
a result of booze.

47:27.083 --> 47:31.542
I'm just now feeling like
I'm beating my heroin addiction.

47:31.542 --> 47:34.166
To go back home
to alcohol?

47:35.166 --> 47:36.250
- Okay.

47:37.333 --> 47:39.126
- Don't be mad.

47:39.126 --> 47:40.126
- I'm not mad.

47:40.126 --> 47:41.209
- Yeah, you are.

47:41.209 --> 47:42.792
- No, it was
a stupid idea.

47:42.792 --> 47:44.792
I just didn't
think things through.

47:44.792 --> 47:46.375
That's my problem.

47:46.375 --> 47:49.458
I don't think anything
all the fucking way through.

47:51.084 --> 47:53.542
- I hate when you're
self-deprecating.

47:53.542 --> 47:55.458
It's so cute.

47:58.001 --> 48:00.458
Hey, where'd you get
that stuff anyway?

48:00.458 --> 48:03.167
- A friend of mine in Unit B
rigged up a still.

48:12.001 --> 48:15.084
♪ ♪

48:15.084 --> 48:17.126
man: [screaming]

48:17.126 --> 48:18.167
[thud]

48:28.375 --> 48:31.084
[faucet running]

48:33.126 --> 48:40.167
♪ ♪

48:53.291 --> 49:00.375
♪ ♪

49:27.583 --> 49:29.166
- So he didn't drink
the moonshine?

49:29.166 --> 49:31.291
- Nope.
- Fuck.

49:31.291 --> 49:33.125
- He was close.

49:33.125 --> 49:36.000
- Close?
Fuck close.

49:36.000 --> 49:38.083
The whole idea here,
the whole beauty of this plan

49:38.083 --> 49:41.583
is that we keep digging up
all the guilt and shame,

49:41.583 --> 49:44.001
all the shit that Beecher's
got inside of him

49:44.001 --> 49:46.042
until he can't
live with himself,

49:46.042 --> 49:48.083
until Beecher
destroys himself.

49:48.083 --> 49:50.458
The alcohol's
the key.

49:50.458 --> 49:52.126
- No, Vern,
I'm the key.

49:52.126 --> 49:53.625
Beecher loves me.

49:53.625 --> 49:56.291
He won't admit it yet,
but he loves me.

49:56.291 --> 49:59.000
I'll get him
to drink.

49:59.000 --> 50:00.250
- I win.

50:00.250 --> 50:02.000
- Fuck you,
you fucking redneck!

50:02.000 --> 50:04.041
- Eat me, jizzball!

50:04.041 --> 50:06.083
- You'd like that,
wouldn't ya?

50:07.542 --> 50:09.208
Fucking asshole.

50:09.208 --> 50:11.125
- What the fuck
was that about?

50:11.125 --> 50:13.166
- Who the fuck knows.

50:13.166 --> 50:15.792
I hate what
that cocksucker did to you.

50:19.126 --> 50:20.167
- Come on.

50:25.126 --> 50:26.208
- Cocksucker!

50:31.209 --> 50:32.500
I don't understand,

50:32.500 --> 50:34.375
your parents decide

50:34.375 --> 50:36.500
whether or not you get
to see your own kids?

50:36.500 --> 50:37.875
- No.

50:37.875 --> 50:39.834
They think,
all things considered,

50:39.834 --> 50:42.209
I shouldn't spend time
with them yet.

50:42.209 --> 50:44.417
Seeing me like this might do
more harm than good.

50:44.417 --> 50:47.250
- Seeing you like this,
what the fuck does that mean?

50:47.250 --> 50:49.667
- You know.

50:49.667 --> 50:52.209
- Beecher,
you're their father.

50:54.084 --> 50:56.126
For Chrissakes, everything
that they've been through,

50:56.126 --> 50:59.750
finding your wife,
their mother, dead.

51:01.667 --> 51:04.917
They need you,
not their grandparents.

51:04.917 --> 51:06.083
You.

51:06.083 --> 51:07.500
- You think?

51:07.500 --> 51:10.001
- Despite everything
that you've gone through,

51:10.001 --> 51:11.625
one thing
hasn't changed.

51:11.625 --> 51:14.001
They are your blood.

51:21.834 --> 51:22.875
- Hey.
- [gasps]

51:23.542 --> 51:25.750
Daddy,
Daddy, Daddy!

51:29.000 --> 51:31.208
I miss you, Daddy.

51:36.834 --> 51:38.625
- I love you, Daddy.

51:42.458 --> 51:44.208
- [laughs]

51:44.208 --> 51:46.959
- You're doing
laundry?

51:46.959 --> 51:48.333
- Yeah.

51:48.333 --> 51:50.333
- You hate
doing laundry.

51:50.333 --> 51:52.792
- Yeah.
- Chris.

51:52.792 --> 51:54.583
- I'm celebrating
your reunion.

51:54.583 --> 51:56.041
- Are you nuts?
They're gonna see you.

51:56.041 --> 51:57.750
- I don't care!

51:57.750 --> 51:59.667
- All right.

51:59.667 --> 52:01.792
- You look good
without a beard.

52:01.792 --> 52:03.500
- What happened?

52:05.126 --> 52:06.709
- Ah...

52:10.001 --> 52:12.084
- What? What?

52:12.084 --> 52:14.542
- Remember I told you I got
married three times?

52:14.542 --> 52:17.042
Four times,
if you count...

52:18.709 --> 52:20.792
Bonnie,
who I married twice.

52:20.792 --> 52:22.333
- Uh-huh.

52:22.333 --> 52:24.875
Why did you get married
so often?

52:24.875 --> 52:26.208
- Call me old-fashioned,

52:26.208 --> 52:28.250
but before I fuck them,
I marry them.

52:28.917 --> 52:29.917
- [laughs]

52:29.917 --> 52:32.750
- The problem is...

52:35.458 --> 52:37.166
The sex.

52:38.875 --> 52:42.167
It's never as good
as it is in the beginning,

52:42.167 --> 52:44.375
and once
the sex sucks,

52:44.375 --> 52:47.458
I realize I got nothing
in common with them.

52:50.083 --> 52:53.458
- Genevieve and I had
everything in common until...

53:01.333 --> 53:03.125
- Bonnie just
got married again.

53:05.167 --> 53:07.417
I shouldn't care, right?

53:07.417 --> 53:12.208
I divorced her twice,
right?

53:12.208 --> 53:13.667
I got no claim on her.

53:18.000 --> 53:19.041
Bitch.

53:21.583 --> 53:22.834
- Come here.

53:28.084 --> 53:29.792
Get the fuck over here.

53:51.167 --> 53:53.001
I love you.

53:59.959 --> 54:01.917
- I love you, Toby.

54:13.834 --> 54:14.875
♪ ♪

54:14.875 --> 54:17.709
Fuck you!
Fuck you!

54:19.583 --> 54:21.125
